OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1772168422
OL,3,CLandscape by Sir Winston Churchill to
OL,4,Cgo on display in UK for first time
OL,6,FSir Winston gifted the painting to his
OL,7,Ffriend Lord Beaverbrook for his 80th
OL,8,Fbirthday in 1959 and it is currently
OL,9,Fon loan from the Beaverbrook Canadian
OL,10,FFoundation.
OL,12,FKatherine Carter, property curator at
OL,13,FChartwell, said: "Churchill once said
OL,14,F'the muse of painting came to my
OL,15,Frescue'. It was his way of getting
OL,16,Faway from the stresses and strains of
OL,17,Fpublic and political life.
OL,26,@uD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/5
